contentrichtext.text: {{Infobox French commune |name = Quincy-Voisins |latitude = 48.8983 |longitude = 2.8833 |INSEE = 77382 |postal code = 77860 |region = [[Île-de-France (region)|Île-de-France]] |department = [[Seine-et-Marne]] |arrondissement = Meaux |canton = Crécy-la-Chapelle |mayor = Jean-Jacques Jego |term = 2008–2014 |intercommunality = |elevation min m = 43 |elevation max m = 138 |area km2 = 10.33 |population = 4982 |population date = 2006 }} '''Quincy-Voisins''' is a [[Communes of France|commune]] in the [[Seine-et-Marne]] [[Departments of France|department]] in the [[Île-de-France (region)|Île-de-France]] [[Regions of France|region]] in north-central [[France]]. ==Demographics== The inhabitants are called ''Quincéens''. ==Twin towns== The town is [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with the village of [[Braunston]] in Northamptonshire, England. ==See also== *[[Communes of the Seine-et-Marne department]] ==References== *[http://www.insee.fr/en/home/home_page.asp INSEE] {{Reflist}} ==External links== *[http://www.iaurif.org/en/gis/fichescom/mos99/ficmos/mos77382.html 1999 Land Use, from IAURIF (Institute for Urban Planning and Development of the Paris-Île-de-France région)] {{en}} *[http://www.culture.gouv.fr/public/mistral/merimee_fr?ACTION=CHERCHER&FIELD_98=INSEE&VALUE_98=77382 French Ministry of Culture list for Quincy-Voisins] {{Fr}} *[http://www.viamichelin.co.uk/viamichelin/gbr/dyn/controller/mapPerformPage?strAddress=&strCP=77860&strLocation=Quincy-Voisins&strCountry=1424&image2.x=28&image2.y=7 Map of Quincy-Voisins on Michelin] {{en}} {{Seine-et-Marne communes}} {{DEFAULTSORT:Quincyvoisins}} [[Category:Communes of Seine-et-Marne]] {{SeineMarne-geo-stub}}
